			<h4><a rel="nofollow" id="comment_link_65484848" name="comment_link_65484848" href="//it.slashdot.org/comments.pl?sid=23731382&amp;cid=65484848" onclick="return D2.setFocusComment(65484848)" >The problem isn't AI...</a>


		 	<span id="comment_score_65484848" class="score"> (<a href="#" onclick="getModalPrefs('modcommentlog', 'Moderation Comment Log', 65484848); return false"><span class=opt>Score:</span>3</a>)</span></h4>
		</div>
		<div class="details">
			<span class="by"><span class="byby">by </span><a rel="nofollow" href="//slashdot.org/~sarren1901">sarren1901</a>  <span class="uid"><a rel="nofollow" href="//slashdot.org/~sarren1901">( 5415506 )</a></span></a></span><span class="writes" style="display:none"> writes:</span> 
			<span class="otherdetails" id="comment_otherdetails_65484848">		
		on Sunday June 29, 2025 @06:38PM (<span class="ind"></span><a rel="nofollow" href="//it.slashdot.org/comments.pl?sid=23731382&amp;cid=65484848">#65484848</a>)
		<small> </small>
</span>
		</div>
	</div>
	<div class="commentBody">
		<div id="comment_body_65484848"><p>But rather all the jobs it could potentially decimate. People don't want to work, we have to work. If AI takes enough jobs without offering us more jobs, our social system won't be able to support us.</p><p>If all the benefits of AI were equally spread out to everyone, then people would be a lot less concerned. Unfortunately for us, we live in a system that expects work for food, housing and clothes. Don't work, you are going to suffer.</p><p>Given how things have gone the past 50 years, it's no mystery why people are nervous about AI. We know our system will leave us behind.</p></div>
	</div>

